parties.raw_snippet:
between
Rogers Cable Communications Inc. (“Rogers”) and
EuroMedia Holdings Corp. (“Licensor”) offering EurocinemaSM Video-on-Demand service
made as of July 11 , 2006 (the “Effective Date”)
parties.reasoning: The header of the document explicitly states the agreement is between Rogers Cable Communications Inc. (identified as “Rogers”) and EuroMedia Holdings Corp. (identified as “Licensor”). These are the two contracting parties named in the agreement header.

contract_type.reasoning: The agreement grants Licensor to Rogers a non-exclusive license and right to distribute and exhibit entertainment programming on a Video-on-Demand basis, and sets out license fees and licensing terms. The core economic substance is licensing content for VOD distribution (granting distribution/exhibition rights and payment of license fees), which corresponds to a License Agreement.

notice_period.reasoning: The contract does not impose an advance notice requirement to PREVENT an automatic renewal. Renewal is "At Rogers’ option" (Section 7), not automatic, so there is no notice period to prevent automatic renewal. (Section 7 does include a separate 60-day notice right to terminate continuation after expiry, but that is not a notice-to-prevent-auto-renewal clause.)

expiration_date.raw_snippet: The term of this Agreement (the “Initial Term”) shall commence as of the Effective Date and, unless earlier terminated in accordance with this Agreement, shall terminate on June 30, 2010.
expiration_date.reasoning: Section 7 expressly sets the Initial Term and gives a specific calendar termination date of June 30, 2010 for the Initial Term. This is an explicit expiration date.

renewal_term.raw_snippet: At Rogers’ option, this Agreement shall renew for a subsequent term of two (2) years on the terms and conditions herein (the “Renewal Term”).
renewal_term.reasoning: Section 7 states that, at Rogers' option, the agreement may renew for a subsequent term of two (2) years. This specifies the renewal duration and that renewal is exercisable by Rogers.

agreement_date.reasoning: The header states the agreement was "made as of July 11 , 2006" and labels that date as the Effective Date. This phrase indicates when the agreement was made/signed.

effective_date.reasoning: The same header phrase explicitly defines July 11, 2006 as "the Effective Date." Therefore the agreement takes effect on that date.

governing_law.raw_snippet: This Agreement shall be governed by laws of the Province of Ontario and the federal laws of Canada applicable therein. The parties hereby attorn to the non-exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of the Province of Ontario. This Section shall survive the termination or expiration of this Agreement.
governing_law.reasoning: Section 23 is the governing law clause and explicitly states the agreement is governed by the laws of the Province of Ontario (and applicable federal laws of Canada). The jurisdiction reference identifies Ontario as the governing jurisdiction.
